# Session log (SESSION_LOG.md)

The maintainer relies on **`SESSION_LOG.md`** staying current when work is merged or pushed. They will forget to update it—the agent must not.

## When to update

Whenever this repo gets **meaningful changes** (features, fixes, new routes, env/setup shifts, notable refactors), **append or edit `SESSION_LOG.md`** in the same change batch—preferably **before** committing or advising a push.

## What to include

- **Date** (and short session title if helpful).
- **Summary bullets** of what changed and why it matters.
- **Files touched** (added / updated) when useful for handoff.
- **Operational notes** (env vars, restart steps, deploy caveats) when relevant.

## Out of scope

- Do not log trivial one-line typo fixes unless the user asks.
- Never commit **`.env.local`**—session log may mention env **names** only.
